h3. Ingredients

* ½ pound whole cashews*
* 2 Tablespoon butter, ghee, or olive oil
* 5 shallots, thinly sliced
* 5 curry leaves
* 2-in piece of lemongrass or zest of one lemon
* 1 Tablespoon coriander
* ½ Teaspoon turmeric
* ½ Teaspoon salt
* 2 chiles, thinly sliced
* 2 cloves garlic, minced
* 2 slices ginger
* 15 oz unsweetened coconut milk
* 2 Tablespoon cilantro, chopped

h3. Method

Sauté the shallots in the butter or oil, stirring occasionally, until golden,
about 10 minutes.

Add the curry, lemon, turmeric, chiles, garlic, ginger, and salt, and cook
until fragrant, 5-10 minutes.

Add remaining ingredients and simmer until thickened, another 5-10 minutes.
Remove curry leaves and serve, with rice.
